g.text: A week of evidences In depth in the Humanitarian Encyclopedia

As part of the Humanitarian Evidence Week, we will explain how the Humanitarian Encyclopedia in-tends to gather and analyse the diversity of humanitarian languages.From November 7th to 12th 2017, we has delivered, three times a day, initial evidence on the variation of terms used in humanitarian action. Based on an analysis of the geographical, sectoral and organisa-tional diversity of actors intervening in crisis contexts, we has explored how this diversity is reected in the wayBe more than a spectator of the show: the Humanitarian Encyclopedia is a collaborative project enga-ging humanitarian actors and researchers alike.
